Market Analysis and Insights

Mobile Encryption Market

Increased proliferation of smartphones and tablets across enterprises, growing concerns related to data security or privacy of data, and increasing application of mobile encryption by a wide range of end user verticals such as banking, financial services, and insurance, aerospace and defense, healthcare, government and public sector, telecommunications and IT, retail and others are the major factors attributable to the growth of mobile encryption market. Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the mobile encryption market will exhibit a CAGR of 30.68% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. This means that the mobile encryption market would stand tall at a market value of USD 10,128.91 million by 2028.

From the name itself, it is clear that mobile encryption is the technology of encrypting and encoding the user data using symmetric encryption keys. In other words, mobile encryption limits the unauthorized access into the devices.

Increased use of mobile devices, especially the developing ones, and rising concerns towards the sensitivity of data will emerge as the major mobile encryption market growth driving factors. Increasing demand for internet of things technology coupled with rising adoption of advanced technologies such as artificial intelligence will further aggravate the demand for mobile encryption. Need for stringent compliance and regulatory requirement is another factor bolstering the growth of mobile encryption market.

However, absence of trained workforce or skilled expertise will act as a growth restraint for the mobile encryption market. High operation expenditure will further dampen the growth rate of the mobile encryption market.

